---
source: crates/flight-core/tests/core_snapshots.rs
expression: output
---
[CFG-001] Config file missing — The configuration file was not found at the expected path.
Resolution: Create a default config file or specify the path explicitly.

[CFG-002] Config parse error — The configuration file contains invalid syntax.
Resolution: Validate the file with a TOML/JSON linter.

[CFG-003] Config value out of range — A configuration value is outside its acceptable range.
Resolution: Consult docs/reference for valid ranges.

[CFG-004] Config migration required — The config file uses a deprecated schema version.
Resolution: Run `flightctl config migrate` to update.

[DEV-001] Device not found — The requested HID device could not be located on any USB bus.
Resolution: Reconnect the device and check USB cables.

[DEV-002] Device open failed — The operating system refused to open the HID device.
Resolution: Run as administrator or check udev rules on Linux.

[DEV-003] Device read timeout — No data received from device within the expected interval.
Resolution: Check device firmware and USB connection.

[DEV-004] Device write failed — Failed to send data to the HID device.
Resolution: Verify device supports output reports and is connected.

[DEV-005] Calibration data missing — No calibration data found for this device.
Resolution: Run the calibration wizard for this device.

[INT-001] RT spine overrun — The RT tick exceeded its time budget.
Resolution: Check system load and disable non-essential plugins.

[INT-002] Bus queue full — A lock-free queue dropped messages due to overflow.
Resolution: Reduce producer rate or increase queue capacity in config.

[INT-003] Unexpected state — An internal state machine reached an unexpected state.
Resolution: File a bug report with diagnostic bundle attached.

[INT-004] Allocation in RT path — A heap allocation was detected on the RT hot path.
Resolution: This is a bug — report it with a backtrace.

[NET-001] gRPC bind failed — The IPC server could not bind to the requested port.
Resolution: Check if the port is already in use.

[NET-002] gRPC connection refused — Could not connect to the gRPC endpoint.
Resolution: Ensure flightd is running and the port is correct.

[NET-003] TLS handshake failed — The TLS handshake with the remote endpoint failed.
Resolution: Verify certificates and TLS configuration.

[NET-004] Cloud sync failed — Profile cloud synchronisation failed.
Resolution: Check internet connectivity and authentication.

[PLG-001] Plugin load failed — The plugin could not be loaded from disk.
Resolution: Verify plugin file exists and is a valid WASM/native module.

[PLG-002] Plugin capability denied — The plugin requested a capability it is not allowed.
Resolution: Review plugin manifest and grant required capabilities.

[PLG-003] Plugin timeout — The plugin exceeded its per-tick time budget.
Resolution: Optimise the plugin or increase the budget in config.

[PLG-004] Plugin panic — The plugin panicked during execution.
Resolution: Check plugin logs and report the bug to the plugin author.

[PRF-001] Profile parse error — The profile JSON/TOML could not be parsed.
Resolution: Validate profile syntax with the profile linter.

[PRF-002] Profile schema invalid — The profile does not conform to the expected schema.
Resolution: Compare against the profile JSON schema in docs/reference.

[PRF-003] Profile merge conflict — Two profiles define conflicting axis assignments.
Resolution: Resolve overlapping assignments in the more-specific profile.

[PRF-004] Profile not found — The specified profile file does not exist.
Resolution: Check the profile path and file name.

[SIM-001] SimConnect unavailable — The MSFS SimConnect library could not be loaded.
Resolution: Ensure MSFS is installed and SimConnect SDK is available.

[SIM-002] Sim connection lost — The connection to the simulator was unexpectedly closed.
Resolution: Restart the simulator and reconnect.

[SIM-003] Sim variable not found — The requested simulator variable does not exist.
Resolution: Check variable name against the sim's SDK documentation.

[SIM-004] Sim version mismatch — The simulator version is not compatible with this adapter.
Resolution: Update OpenFlight or check compatibility matrix.

[SVC-001] Service start failed — The flightd daemon could not start.
Resolution: Check logs for port conflicts or permission issues.

[SVC-002] Instance lock held — Another flightd instance is already running.
Resolution: Stop the existing instance before starting a new one.

[SVC-003] Graceful shutdown timeout — The service did not shut down within the allowed time.
Resolution: Force-kill the process and check for stuck tasks.

[SVC-004] Health check failed — One or more subsystem health checks returned unhealthy.
Resolution: Run diagnostic bundle and inspect component status.
